"AWSTemplateFormatVersion: \"2010-09-09\"\nDescription: >\n  Luciel CloudWatch alarm pack. Step 28: 3 worker metric filters +\n  7 alarms (worker liveness/health/errors, RDS connections/CPU/storage,\n  SSM failures). Arc 9 C7 extension: 4 backend metric filters + 4\n  alarms (audit-immutability tamper [High], GUC-leak guard [High],\n  ops-role connect velocity [Medium], audit-write velocity [Medium]),\n  plus PD SNS-HTTPS subscription resolved from SSM. Region\n  ca-central-1, account 729005488042. Full design notes in\n  docs/runbooks/arc9-c7-observability.md and the docs/runbooks/\n  step-28-phase-2-deploy.md.\n\nParameters:\n  AlertEmail:\n    Type: String\n    Default: aryans.www@gmail.com\n    Description: >\n      Email address for alarm notifications. After stack create the\n      address will receive an SNS confirmation email - the subscription\n      stays in PendingConfirmation until that link is clicked.\n  WorkerLogGroupName:\n    Type: String\n    Default: /ecs/luciel-worker\n    Description: CloudWatch Logs group for the worker service.\n  WorkerClusterName:\n    Type: String\n    Default: luciel-cluster\n    Description: ECS cluster hosting luciel-worker-service.\n  WorkerServiceName:\n    Type: String\n    Default: luciel-worker-service\n    Description: ECS service running the celery worker.\n  RdsInstanceIdentifier:\n    Type: String\n    Default: luciel-db\n    Description: RDS DBInstanceIdentifier (verified via describe-db-instances 2026-05-05).\n  RdsConnectionThreshold:\n    Type: Number\n    Default: 90\n    Description: 80% of max_connections (~112) on db.t3.micro.\n  RdsCpuThresholdPercent:\n    Type: Number\n    Default: 85\n    Description: CPU utilization percent that triggers the alarm.\n  RdsFreeStorageThresholdBytes:\n    Type: Number\n    Default: 4294967296\n    Description: 4 GiB free space floor on the 20 GiB RDS volume.\n  WorkerErrorThreshold:\n    Type: Number\n    Default: 5\n    Description: ERROR log lines per 5 min that trigger the alarm.\n\n  # ------------------------------------------------------------------\n  # Arc 9 C7 parameters\n  # ------------------------------------------------------------------\n  BackendLogGroupName:\n    Type: String\n    Default: /ecs/luciel-backend\n    Description: >\n      CloudWatch Logs group for the FastAPI backend service. The\n      Arc 9 C7 metric filters parse audit-immutability denials,\n      ops-role connect events, GUC-leak guard violations, and\n      per-admin audit-log write events from this group.\n  PagerDutyServiceKeySsmParam:\n    Type: String\n    Default: /luciel/prod/pagerduty/integration_url\n    Description: >\n      SSM parameter NAME that holds the PagerDuty Events-API v2\n      integration URL (HTTPS endpoint). The PagerDuty SNS-HTTPS\n      subscription resolves the parameter at stack-deploy time via\n      ``{{resolve:ssm:NAME:VERSION}}`` -- which means the URL never\n      lives in this repo, never lives in the CloudFormation\n      parameter overrides log, and is opaque to anyone who only has\n      describe-stacks access. Rotating the URL is a put-parameter\n      (creates a new SSM version) + update-stack bumping\n      PagerDutyServiceKeySsmVersion. See\n      docs/runbooks/arc9-c7-observability.md for the deploy order.\n\n  PagerDutyServiceKeySsmVersion:\n    Type: String\n    Default: \"1\"\n    AllowedPattern: \"^[1-9][0-9]*$\"\n    Description: >\n      Version number of the SSM parameter named in\n      PagerDutyServiceKeySsmParam to resolve. CFN requires a version\n      pin when the parameter NAME itself is built via Sub ${...}.\n      Bump this on every PD-URL rotation: ``aws ssm put-parameter``\n      creates a new version; then ``aws cloudformation update-stack``\n      with the bumped version makes CFN pick it up. The CFN stack\n      history then records an audit trail of when each PD URL was\n      activated.\n  OpsRoleConnectVelocityThreshold:\n    Type: Number\n    Default: 10\n    Description: >\n      luciel_ops BYPASSRLS connections per 15-minute window that\n      trigger the Medium-severity velocity alarm. Normal cleanup\n      activity is <=2/day, so 10/15min is a generous anomaly floor.\n  AdminAuditWriteVelocityThreshold:\n    Type: Number\n    Default: 50\n    Description: >\n      admin_audit_logs writes per 5-minute window across the whole\n      backend before the Medium-severity velocity alarm fires.\n      Catches mass-mutation runaways (cascade bugs, accidental bulk\n      ops, compromised-admin runs).\n\nResources:\n\n  AlertTopic:\n    Type: AWS::SNS::Topic\n    Properties:\n      TopicName: luciel-prod-alerts\n      DisplayName: Luciel Prod Alerts\n\n  AlertEmailSubscription:\n    Type: AWS::SNS::Subscription\n    Properties:\n      TopicArn: !Ref AlertTopic\n      Protocol: email\n      Endpoint: !Ref AlertEmail\n\n  # ------------------------------------------------------------------\n  # Log MetricFilters on /ecs/luciel-worker\n  # ------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n  HeartbeatMetricFilter:\n    Type: AWS::Logs::MetricFilter\n    Properties:\n      LogGroupName: !Ref WorkerLogGroupName\n      FilterName: luciel-worker-heartbeat-touched\n      FilterPattern: '\"healthcheck heartbeat: touched\"'\n      MetricTransformations:\n        - MetricNamespace: Luciel/Worker\n          MetricName: HeartbeatTouchCount\n          MetricValue: \"1\"\n          DefaultValue: 0\n          Unit: Count\n\n  WorkerErrorMetricFilter:\n    Type: AWS::Logs::MetricFilter\n    Properties:\n      LogGroupName: !Ref WorkerLogGroupName\n      FilterName: luciel-worker-error-lines\n      FilterPattern: '?ERROR ?Error ?error'\n      MetricTransformations:\n        - MetricNamespace: Luciel/Worker\n          MetricName: ErrorLogLineCount\n          MetricValue: \"1\"\n          DefaultValue: 0\n          Unit: Count\n\n  SsmAccessDeniedMetricFilter:\n    Type: AWS::Logs::MetricFilter\n    Properties:\n      LogGroupName: !Ref WorkerLogGroupName\n      FilterName: luciel-worker-ssm-access-denied\n      FilterPattern: '?AccessDeniedException ?\"is not authorized to perform: ssm:\" ?ParameterNotFound'\n      MetricTransformations:\n        - MetricNamespace: Luciel/Worker\n          MetricName: SsmAccessFailureCount\n          MetricValue: \"1\"\n          DefaultValue: 0\n          Unit: Count\n\n  # ------------------------------------------------------------------\n  # Alarms\n  # ------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n  WorkerNoHeartbeatAlarm:\n    Type: AWS::CloudWatch::Alarm\n    DependsOn: HeartbeatMetricFilter\n    Properties:\n      AlarmName: luciel-worker-no-heartbeat\n      AlarmDescription: >\n        Worker producer-heartbeat (Commit 7 rev 11) emits\n        \"healthcheck heartbeat: touched\" every 15s, so a healthy\n        worker produces ~4 events per 60s window. Alarm fires when\n        4 of 5 consecutive 60s windows have fewer than 1 heartbeat\n        (i.e. ~4-5min outage tolerated for one transient ingestion\n        glitch). CloudWatch alarm Period must be 10/20/30 or a\n        multiple of 60; 60 is the smallest legal value that gives\n        sub-1min granularity. Strongest worker-liveness signal in\n        the system.\n      Namespace: Luciel/Worker\n      MetricName: HeartbeatTouchCount\n      Statistic: Sum\n      Period: 60\n      EvaluationPeriods: 5\n      DatapointsToAlarm: 4\n      Threshold: 1\n      ComparisonOperator: LessThanThreshold\n      TreatMissingData: breaching\n      AlarmActions:\n        - !Ref AlertTopic\n      OKActions:\n        - !Ref AlertTopic\n\n  WorkerUnhealthyTaskCountAlarm:\n    Type: AWS::CloudWatch::Alarm\n    Properties:\n      AlarmName: luciel-worker-unhealthy-task-count\n      AlarmDescription: >\n        ECS worker service running task count drops below 1 for two\n        consecutive 1-minute periods. Catches the case where the\n        service is down even before the heartbeat alarm sees missed\n        windows. RunningTaskCount is emitted by Container Insights\n        (ECS/ContainerInsights namespace), NOT by the default AWS/ECS\n        namespace -- using AWS/ECS here was a silent miswire that\n        produced INSUFFICIENT_DATA -> Breaching alarm storms.\n      Namespace: ECS/ContainerInsights\n      MetricName: RunningTaskCount\n      Dimensions:\n        - Name: ClusterName\n          Value: !Ref WorkerClusterName\n        - Name: ServiceName\n          Value: !Ref WorkerServiceName\n      Statistic: Average\n      Period: 60\n      EvaluationPeriods: 2\n      DatapointsToAlarm: 2\n      Threshold: 1\n      ComparisonOperator: LessThanThreshold\n      TreatMissingData: breaching\n      AlarmActions:\n        - !Ref AlertTopic\n      OKActions:\n        - !Ref AlertTopic\n\n  WorkerErrorLogRateAlarm:\n    Type: AWS::CloudWatch::Alarm\n    DependsOn: WorkerErrorMetricFilter\n    Properties:\n      AlarmName: luciel-worker-error-log-rate\n      AlarmDescription: >\n        More than 5 ERROR log lines in two consecutive 5-minute windows.\n        Surfaces sustained worker failure modes (DB pool exhaustion,\n        broker churn, retention purge errors, etc.) without paging on\n        a single transient blip.\n      Namespace: Luciel/Worker\n      MetricName: ErrorLogLineCount\n      Statistic: Sum\n      Period: 300\n      EvaluationPeriods: 2\n      DatapointsToAlarm: 2\n      Threshold: !Ref WorkerErrorThreshold\n      ComparisonOperator: GreaterThanThreshold\n      TreatMissingData: notBreaching\n      AlarmActions:\n        - !Ref AlertTopic\n      OKActions:\n        - !Ref AlertTopic\n\n  RdsConnectionCountAlarm:\n    Type: AWS::CloudWatch::Alarm\n    Properties:\n      AlarmName: luciel-rds-connection-count\n      AlarmDescription: >\n        RDS DatabaseConnections sustained above 80% of max_connections\n        (~90 of ~112) for 5 minutes. Pre-revenue load profile should\n        keep this near zero - any sustained breach is a leak signal.\n      Namespace: AWS/RDS\n      MetricName: DatabaseConnections\n      Dimensions:\n        - Name: DBInstanceIdentifier\n          Value: !Ref RdsInstanceIdentifier\n      Statistic: Average\n      Period: 300\n      EvaluationPeriods: 1\n      DatapointsToAlarm: 1\n      Threshold: !Ref RdsConnectionThreshold\n      ComparisonOperator: GreaterThanThreshold\n      TreatMissingData: notBreaching\n      AlarmActions:\n        - !Ref AlertTopic\n      OKActions:\n        - !Ref AlertTopic\n\n  RdsCpuAlarm:\n    Type: AWS::CloudWatch::Alarm\n    Properties:\n      AlarmName: luciel-rds-cpu\n      AlarmDescription: >\n        RDS CPU above 85% for 10 minutes. db.t3.micro is burstable\n        (20% baseline) so sustained breach signals either credit\n        exhaustion or actual workload pressure - either deserves paging\n        before queries start timing out.\n      Namespace: AWS/RDS\n      MetricName: CPUUtilization\n      Dimensions:\n        - Name: DBInstanceIdentifier\n          Value: !Ref RdsInstanceIdentifier\n      Statistic: Average\n      Period: 300\n      EvaluationPeriods: 2\n      DatapointsToAlarm: 2\n      Threshold: !Ref RdsCpuThresholdPercent\n      ComparisonOperator: GreaterThanThreshold\n      TreatMissingData: notBreaching\n      AlarmActions:\n        - !Ref AlertTopic\n      OKActions:\n        - !Ref AlertTopic\n\n  RdsFreeStorageAlarm:\n    Type: AWS::CloudWatch::Alarm\n    Properties:\n      AlarmName: luciel-rds-free-storage\n      AlarmDescription: >\n        RDS FreeStorageSpace falls below 4 GiB on the 20 GiB volume\n        (i.e. 80% used). Page well before RDS auto-scales storage so\n        we have time to investigate audit-log growth or unexpected\n        retention regressions.\n      Namespace: AWS/RDS\n      MetricName: FreeStorageSpace\n      Dimensions:\n        - Name: DBInstanceIdentifier\n          Value: !Ref RdsInstanceIdentifier\n      Statistic: Average\n      Period: 900\n      EvaluationPeriods: 1\n      DatapointsToAlarm: 1\n      Threshold: !Ref RdsFreeStorageThresholdBytes\n      ComparisonOperator: LessThanThreshold\n      TreatMissingData: notBreaching\n      AlarmActions:\n        - !Ref AlertTopic\n      OKActions:\n        - !Ref AlertTopic\n\n  SsmAccessFailureAlarm:\n    Type: AWS::CloudWatch::Alarm\n    DependsOn: SsmAccessDeniedMetricFilter\n    Properties:\n      AlarmName: luciel-ssm-getparameter-failures\n      AlarmDescription: >\n        Any SSM GetParameter access failure (AccessDeniedException,\n        ParameterNotFound, or \"is not authorized to perform: ssm:\")\n        on /ecs/luciel-worker over a 5-minute window. Catches IAM\n        drift and parameter-deletion regressions before they cascade\n        into worker-down.\n      Namespace: Luciel/Worker\n      MetricName: SsmAccessFailureCount\n      Statistic: Sum\n      Period: 300\n      EvaluationPeriods: 1\n      DatapointsToAlarm: 1\n      Threshold: 0\n      ComparisonOperator: GreaterThanThreshold\n      TreatMissingData: notBreaching\n      AlarmActions:\n        - !Ref AlertTopic\n      OKActions:\n        - !Ref AlertTopic\n\n  # ==================================================================\n  # Arc 9 C7 -- Backend observability for tenant isolation\n  # ==================================================================\n  #\n  # Doctrine references:\n  #   D7.1 -- Every grant the ops role exercises emits a CloudWatch event\n  #   D7.2 -- Every denial by an immutability policy emits a\n  #           High-severity alarm\n  #\n  # The two High-severity alarms (AuditLogIntegrityBreach,\n  # GUCLeakGuardViolation) publish to BOTH AlertTopic (SNS email)\n  # and PagerDutyTopic (SNS HTTPS to PD Events API v2). Medium\n  # alarms publish only to AlertTopic.\n  #\n  # All four metric filters parse /ecs/luciel-backend; the worker\n  # log group is untouched.\n\n  PagerDutyTopic:\n    Type: AWS::SNS::Topic\n    Properties:\n      TopicName: luciel-prod-pagerduty-high\n      DisplayName: Luciel Prod High-Severity (PagerDuty)\n\n  PagerDutySubscription:\n    Type: AWS::SNS::Subscription\n    Properties:\n      TopicArn: !Ref PagerDutyTopic\n      Protocol: https\n      # Resolved at stack deploy from the SSM parameter named in\n      # PagerDutyServiceKeySsmParam, pinned at the version named in\n      # PagerDutyServiceKeySsmVersion. The value at that parameter\n      # is the PagerDuty Events API v2 integration URL, e.g.\n      #   https://events.pagerduty.com/integration/<key>/enqueue\n      #\n      # CFN requires a VERSION pin when the SSM resolver name is\n      # itself built via Sub ${...}. This is actually a useful\n      # operational property: rotating the PD URL is a two-step\n      # ritual -- (1) ``aws ssm put-parameter`` (creates v+1), then\n      # (2) ``aws cloudformation update-stack`` with\n      # PagerDutyServiceKeySsmVersion=v+1. The CFN history then\n      # carries an audit trail of every PD URL rotation tied to a\n      # stack-update timestamp.\n      #\n      # If the parameter is empty at deploy time the stack fails;\n      # see docs/runbooks/arc9-c7-observability.md for the bootstrap\n      # sequence.\n      # NOTE: plain ``ssm`` resolver, not ``ssm-secure``. CFN does\n      # not support ssm-secure on AWS::SNS::Subscription/Endpoint\n      # (only RDS MasterUserPassword and a small allowlist of other\n      # secret-shaped properties accept it). The PD integration URL\n      # is therefore stored as a String SSM parameter, not a\n      # SecureString. Access control falls to IAM on the SSM\n      # parameter path -- the URL never reaches the repo or the\n      # describe-stacks output and is only readable by principals\n      # with ssm:GetParameter on /luciel/prod/pagerduty/*.\n      #\n      # Worst-case compromise impact is limited: the URL is a\n      # write-only event ingest, not a credential. An attacker with\n      # it can spam PD incidents but cannot read or exfiltrate\n      # anything from PD, AWS, or Luciel.\n      Endpoint: !Sub \"{{resolve:ssm:${PagerDutyServiceKeySsmParam}:${PagerDutyServiceKeySsmVersion}}}\"\n      DeliveryPolicy:\n        healthyRetryPolicy:\n          numRetries: 3\n          minDelayTarget: 5\n          maxDelayTarget: 30\n          numMinDelayRetries: 1\n          numMaxDelayRetries: 1\n          backoffFunction: exponential\n\n  # ------------------------------------------------------------------\n  # C7 MetricFilters on /ecs/luciel-backend\n  # ------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n  AdminAuditLogWriteMetricFilter:\n    Type: AWS::Logs::MetricFilter\n    Properties:\n      LogGroupName: !Ref BackendLogGroupName\n      FilterName: luciel-backend-admin-audit-log-write\n      # The repositories.audit_chain before_flush listener emits a\n      # debug line containing \"admin_audit_logs chain row=\" for\n      # each row hashed and persisted. We match on the substring\n      # \"admin_audit_logs chain row=\" so the count tracks the\n      # number of audit rows landed (not the number of API calls\n      # that happened to touch the table without inserting).\n      FilterPattern: '\"admin_audit_logs chain row=\"'\n      MetricTransformations:\n        - MetricNamespace: Luciel/Backend\n          MetricName: AdminAuditLogWriteCount\n          MetricValue: \"1\"\n          DefaultValue: 0\n          Unit: Count\n\n  OpsRoleConnectMetricFilter:\n    Type: AWS::Logs::MetricFilter\n    Properties:\n      LogGroupName: !Ref BackendLogGroupName\n      FilterName: luciel-backend-ops-role-connect\n      # app.db.session emits exactly this prefix on every\n      # OpsSessionLocal connect (Arc 9 C7.1 listener); the\n      # python-side string is contract-locked with\n      # tests/db/test_c7_1_ops_connect_log_format.py.\n      FilterPattern: '\"arc9.c7.ops_role_connect\"'\n      MetricTransformations:\n        - MetricNamespace: Luciel/Backend\n          MetricName: OpsRoleConnectCount\n          MetricValue: \"1\"\n          DefaultValue: 0\n          Unit: Count\n\n  GUCLeakGuardViolationMetricFilter:\n    Type: AWS::Logs::MetricFilter\n    Properties:\n      LogGroupName: !Ref BackendLogGroupName\n      FilterName: luciel-backend-guc-leak-guard-violation\n      # The C6.4 guard raises AssertionError with the literal\n      # phrase \"OpsSessionLocal must not carry app.admin_id\" when\n      # an ops session is somehow seen with a tenant GUC set.\n      # Any occurrence in prod is structurally impossible (the\n      # sessionmaker boundary makes it so) -- a single hit is a\n      # high-severity invariant violation.\n      FilterPattern: '\"OpsSessionLocal must not carry app.admin_id\"'\n      MetricTransformations:\n        - MetricNamespace: Luciel/Backend\n          MetricName: GUCLeakGuardViolationCount\n          MetricValue: \"1\"\n          DefaultValue: 0\n          Unit: Count\n\n  AuditLogIntegrityBreachMetricFilter:\n    Type: AWS::Logs::MetricFilter\n    Properties:\n      LogGroupName: !Ref BackendLogGroupName\n      FilterName: luciel-backend-audit-log-integrity-breach\n      # Postgres raises errors with code 42501 / message containing\n      # \"new row violates row-level security policy\" or the\n      # C6.2 RESTRICTIVE policy denial phrases. The two strings\n      # below cover both Postgres-level denial messages that fire\n      # when ANYTHING attempts to UPDATE or DELETE admin_audit_logs\n      # (including superuser, including a compromised app role).\n      FilterPattern: '?\"row violates row-level security policy for table \\\"admin_audit_logs\\\"\" ?\"new row violates row-level security policy for table \\\"admin_audit_logs\\\"\"'\n      MetricTransformations:\n        - MetricNamespace: Luciel/Backend\n          MetricName: AuditLogIntegrityBreachCount\n          MetricValue: \"1\"\n          DefaultValue: 0\n          Unit: Count\n\n  # ------------------------------------------------------------------\n  # C7 Alarms\n  # ------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n  AuditLogIntegrityBreachAlarm:\n    Type: AWS::CloudWatch::Alarm\n    DependsOn: AuditLogIntegrityBreachMetricFilter\n    Properties:\n      AlarmName: luciel-audit-log-integrity-breach\n      AlarmDescription: >\n        HIGH SEVERITY (D7.2). The C6.2 RESTRICTIVE policy on\n        admin_audit_logs denied an UPDATE or DELETE attempt. The\n        policy DID block the attempt -- this alarm exists so we\n        learn about the attempt in real time, regardless of the\n        actor (app role, ops role, superuser, compromised\n        credentials). A single occurrence pages.\n      Namespace: Luciel/Backend\n      MetricName: AuditLogIntegrityBreachCount\n      Statistic: Sum\n      Period: 300\n      EvaluationPeriods: 1\n      DatapointsToAlarm: 1\n      Threshold: 0\n      ComparisonOperator: GreaterThanThreshold\n      TreatMissingData: notBreaching\n      AlarmActions:\n        - !Ref AlertTopic\n        - !Ref PagerDutyTopic\n      OKActions:\n        - !Ref AlertTopic\n\n  GUCLeakGuardViolationAlarm:\n    Type: AWS::CloudWatch::Alarm\n    DependsOn: GUCLeakGuardViolationMetricFilter\n    Properties:\n      AlarmName: luciel-guc-leak-guard-violation\n      AlarmDescription: >\n        HIGH SEVERITY (D7.2). The C6.4 GUC-leak guard fired in\n        prod -- meaning an OpsSessionLocal session was opened\n        while a tenant ContextVar was set. This should be\n        structurally impossible (the sessionmaker boundary\n        prevents GUC propagation), so any hit indicates either a\n        framework regression or a manual override. Pages\n        immediately.\n      Namespace: Luciel/Backend\n      MetricName: GUCLeakGuardViolationCount\n      Statistic: Sum\n      Period: 300\n      EvaluationPeriods: 1\n      DatapointsToAlarm: 1\n      Threshold: 0\n      ComparisonOperator: GreaterThanThreshold\n      TreatMissingData: notBreaching\n      AlarmActions:\n        - !Ref AlertTopic\n        - !Ref PagerDutyTopic\n      OKActions:\n        - !Ref AlertTopic\n\n  OpsRoleConnectVelocityAlarm:\n    Type: AWS::CloudWatch::Alarm\n    DependsOn: OpsRoleConnectMetricFilter\n    Properties:\n      AlarmName: luciel-ops-role-connect-velocity\n      AlarmDescription: >\n        MEDIUM SEVERITY (D7.1). luciel_ops BYPASSRLS connections\n        exceeded the velocity threshold in a 15-minute window.\n        Normal ops cleanup is <=2/day; sustained high velocity\n        signals an automation runaway, a debugging session\n        someone forgot to close, or unauthorized access. Pages\n        AlertTopic only (no PagerDuty).\n      Namespace: Luciel/Backend\n      MetricName: OpsRoleConnectCount\n      Statistic: Sum\n      Period: 900\n      EvaluationPeriods: 1\n      DatapointsToAlarm: 1\n      Threshold: !Ref OpsRoleConnectVelocityThreshold\n      ComparisonOperator: GreaterThanThreshold\n      TreatMissingData: notBreaching\n      AlarmActions:\n        - !Ref AlertTopic\n      OKActions:\n        - !Ref AlertTopic\n\n  AdminAuditWriteVelocityAlarm:\n    Type: AWS::CloudWatch::Alarm\n    DependsOn: AdminAuditLogWriteMetricFilter\n    Properties:\n      AlarmName: luciel-admin-audit-write-velocity\n      AlarmDescription: >\n        MEDIUM SEVERITY (D7.1). admin_audit_logs write velocity\n        exceeded the configured threshold in a 5-minute window.\n        Catches cascade bugs, accidental bulk operations, and\n        compromised-admin runs without paging on the steady-state\n        click-by-click admin traffic. Pages AlertTopic only.\n      Namespace: Luciel/Backend\n      MetricName: AdminAuditLogWriteCount\n      Statistic: Sum\n      Period: 300\n      EvaluationPeriods: 1\n      DatapointsToAlarm: 1\n      Threshold: !Ref AdminAuditWriteVelocityThreshold\n      ComparisonOperator: GreaterThanThreshold\n      TreatMissingData: notBreaching\n      AlarmActions:\n        - !Ref AlertTopic\n      OKActions:\n        - !Ref AlertTopic\n\n  # ==================================================================\n  # Arc 9.1 Phase B2 -- G7 per-Admin observability\n  # ==================================================================\n  #\n  # The three alarms below close G7 from the 2026-05-25 prod-alignment\n  # verification: pre-B2, every alarm in this stack was infra-level\n  # (CPU, storage, audit-chain integrity). None of them would fire if\n  # one tenant's traffic was broken while the rest of prod stayed\n  # healthy -- a Customer A 500-rate spike was invisible.\n  #\n  # All three filters key off the JSON payload emitted by\n  # app/middleware/request_logging.py (line ~205):\n  #   {\"evt\":\"http_request\",\"tenant_id\":\"<admin_uuid>\",\n  #    \"status\":<int>,\"duration_ms\":<int>,...}\n  # The JSON-format FilterPattern syntax lets CloudWatch parse the\n  # field and use it as a metric Dimension. That is the per-Admin\n  # pivot that was missing.\n\n  PerAdminHttp5xxMetricFilter:\n    Type: AWS::Logs::MetricFilter\n    Properties:\n      LogGroupName: !Ref BackendLogGroupName\n      FilterName: luciel-backend-per-admin-http-5xx\n      # JSON metric filter: match http_request events with status>=500.\n      # The tenant_id field gets surfaced as a CloudWatch Dimension.\n      FilterPattern: '{ ($.evt = \"http_request\") && ($.status >= 500) && ($.tenant_id = \"*\") }'\n      MetricTransformations:\n        - MetricNamespace: Luciel/Backend\n          MetricName: PerAdminHttp5xxCount\n          MetricValue: \"1\"\n          Unit: Count\n          Dimensions:\n            - Key: AdminId\n              Value: $.tenant_id\n\n  PerAdminHttpLatencyMetricFilter:\n    Type: AWS::Logs::MetricFilter\n    Properties:\n      LogGroupName: !Ref BackendLogGroupName\n      FilterName: luciel-backend-per-admin-http-latency\n      # Same payload, but emit duration_ms as the metric VALUE so\n      # CloudWatch can compute percentiles per Admin.\n      FilterPattern: '{ ($.evt = \"http_request\") && ($.duration_ms = \"*\") && ($.tenant_id = \"*\") }'\n      MetricTransformations:\n        - MetricNamespace: Luciel/Backend\n          MetricName: PerAdminHttpLatencyMs\n          MetricValue: $.duration_ms\n          Unit: Milliseconds\n          Dimensions:\n            - Key: AdminId\n              Value: $.tenant_id\n\n  PerAdminZeroRowMetricFilter:\n    Type: AWS::Logs::MetricFilter\n    Properties:\n      LogGroupName: !Ref BackendLogGroupName\n      FilterName: luciel-backend-per-admin-zero-row\n      # 2xx responses on GET routes (the listing endpoints) where\n      # row_count is 0. This is the \"RLS deny silently\" signature:\n      # a healthy 200 with zero rows where the tenant should have\n      # had data. Requires backend logger to emit row_count -- if\n      # the field is absent the filter never matches, which is\n      # safe (zero datapoints = no alarm rather than false alarm).\n      # Backend code stub to add this field is tracked in the\n      # ARC9_1_ALIGNMENT_CLOSE writeup under \"Phase B2 follow-up\".\n      FilterPattern: '{ ($.evt = \"http_request\") && ($.method = \"GET\") && ($.status = 200) && ($.row_count = 0) && ($.tenant_id = \"*\") }'\n      MetricTransformations:\n        - MetricNamespace: Luciel/Backend\n          MetricName: PerAdminZeroRowCount\n          MetricValue: \"1\"\n          Unit: Count\n          Dimensions:\n            - Key: AdminId\n              Value: $.tenant_id\n\n  # Per-Admin alarm design note (Arc 9.1 Phase B2):\n  #   CloudWatch Standard Alarms do not natively support GROUP BY across\n  #   a metric Dimension -- the closest mechanism is a Metrics Insights\n  #   query inside the alarm's Metrics block, but it must return a SINGLE\n  #   time series (i.e. no multi-series GROUP BY without ORDER BY+LIMIT 1\n  #   inside a downstream aggregation). The pattern below uses Metrics\n  #   Insights to compute the MAX (across all AdminId dimensions) of each\n  #   per-Admin time series, then alarms on that MAX. When ANY Admin's\n  #   counter crosses threshold, the MAX crosses too and the alarm fires.\n  #   The per-Admin pivot is preserved in the underlying metric, so the\n  #   on-call rotation can drill down via the CloudWatch console to\n  #   identify WHICH Admin is the offender once the alarm fires.\n  #\n  # Metrics Insights syntax constraints encountered:\n  #   - p99() is NOT a valid Insights function; use percentile-statistic\n  #     on a single metric instead, which requires a non-Insights metric.\n  #     For latency we therefore use the simpler SELECT MAX(MAX(...)) form\n  #     -- catches the slowest Admin's slowest request in the window.\n  #     A per-Admin true-p99 alarm requires Contributor Insights (which\n  #     is a separate stack and a follow-up).\n  #   - GROUP BY in an alarm context must have ORDER BY + LIMIT to\n  #     collapse to a single series.\n\n  PerAdminHttp5xxAlarm:\n    Type: AWS::CloudWatch::Alarm\n    DependsOn: PerAdminHttp5xxMetricFilter\n    Properties:\n      AlarmName: luciel-per-admin-http-5xx\n      AlarmDescription: >\n        MEDIUM SEVERITY (G7). The maximum-across-all-Admins 5xx-error\n        count in a 5-minute window crossed 5. The CloudWatch console\n        will show which AdminId is the offender (drill into the\n        Luciel/Backend/PerAdminHttp5xxCount metric).\n      Metrics:\n        - Id: e1\n          Expression: \"SELECT MAX(PerAdminHttp5xxCount) FROM SCHEMA(\\\"Luciel/Backend\\\", AdminId) GROUP BY AdminId ORDER BY MAX() DESC LIMIT 1\"\n          Period: 300\n          ReturnData: true\n      EvaluationPeriods: 1\n      DatapointsToAlarm: 1\n      Threshold: 5\n      ComparisonOperator: GreaterThanThreshold\n      TreatMissingData: notBreaching\n      AlarmActions:\n        - !Ref AlertTopic\n      OKActions:\n        - !Ref AlertTopic\n\n  PerAdminHttpP99LatencyAlarm:\n    Type: AWS::CloudWatch::Alarm\n    DependsOn: PerAdminHttpLatencyMetricFilter\n    Properties:\n      AlarmName: luciel-per-admin-http-p99-latency\n      AlarmDescription: >\n        MEDIUM SEVERITY (G7). The maximum-across-all-Admins peak\n        latency in a 5-minute window crossed 5000ms over 2 consecutive\n        windows. This is the slowest-Admin / slowest-request signal;\n        a true per-Admin p99 (rather than peak) requires Contributor\n        Insights -- tracked as a follow-up. Drilling in: open the\n        Luciel/Backend/PerAdminHttpLatencyMs metric and group by AdminId.\n      Metrics:\n        - Id: e1\n          Expression: \"SELECT MAX(PerAdminHttpLatencyMs) FROM SCHEMA(\\\"Luciel/Backend\\\", AdminId) GROUP BY AdminId ORDER BY MAX() DESC LIMIT 1\"\n          Period: 300\n          ReturnData: true\n      EvaluationPeriods: 2\n      DatapointsToAlarm: 2\n      Threshold: 5000\n      ComparisonOperator: GreaterThanThreshold\n      TreatMissingData: notBreaching\n      AlarmActions:\n        - !Ref AlertTopic\n      OKActions:\n        - !Ref AlertTopic\n\n  PerAdminZeroRowAlarm:\n    Type: AWS::CloudWatch::Alarm\n    DependsOn: PerAdminZeroRowMetricFilter\n    Properties:\n      AlarmName: luciel-per-admin-zero-row\n      AlarmDescription: >\n        MEDIUM SEVERITY (G7). The maximum-across-all-Admins zero-row\n        200-OK count in a 5-minute window crossed 10. Signature of\n        an RLS deny-silently regression -- API returns 200 but the\n        GUC mismatch hides the tenant's own data. Requires backend\n        logger to emit row_count on GET responses (Phase B2 follow-up).\n        Until then the filter matches nothing and the alarm sits in\n        INSUFFICIENT_DATA -- TreatMissingData=notBreaching keeps the\n        dashboard tile calm.\n      Metrics:\n        - Id: e1\n          Expression: \"SELECT MAX(PerAdminZeroRowCount) FROM SCHEMA(\\\"Luciel/Backend\\\", AdminId) GROUP BY AdminId ORDER BY MAX() DESC LIMIT 1\"\n          Period: 300\n          ReturnData: true\n      EvaluationPeriods: 1\n      DatapointsToAlarm: 1\n      Threshold: 10\n      ComparisonOperator: GreaterThanThreshold\n      TreatMissingData: notBreaching\n      AlarmActions:\n        - !Ref AlertTopic\n      OKActions:\n        - !Ref AlertTopic\n\nOutputs:\n  AlertTopicArn:\n    Description: ARN of the SNS topic for alarm notifications.\n    Value: !Ref AlertTopic\n    Export:\n      Name: !Sub \"${AWS::StackName}-AlertTopicArn\"\n  HeartbeatMetricNamespace:\n    Description: Custom metric namespace used by Luciel worker filters.\n    Value: Luciel/Worker\n  AlarmsCreated:\n    Description: Number of CloudWatch alarms in this stack.\n    Value: \"14\"\n  PagerDutyTopicArn:\n    Description: ARN of the PagerDuty High-severity SNS topic (Arc 9 C7).\n    Value: !Ref PagerDutyTopic\n    Export:\n      Name: !Sub \"${AWS::StackName}-PagerDutyTopicArn\"\n  BackendMetricNamespace:\n    Description: CloudWatch metric namespace used by Arc 9 C7 backend filters.\n    Value: Luciel/Backend\n"
